# Player Analytics Dashboard

Add a new **"Player Analytics"** page to the GoodGame frontend that displays the same analytics defined in `gold_transformations.py` from the ETL project, computed live from PostgreSQL via new backend API endpoints.

## Context

The `gold_transformations.py` defines 7 Gold-layer analytics in Snowflake:

| # | Gold Table | What it shows |
|---|-----------|---------------|
| 1 | `GOLD_SENTIMENT_PERFORMANCE` | Session data joined with sentiment scores |
| 2 | `GOLD_PLAYER_METRICS` | Per-player aggregates (sessions, max level, avg deaths, playtime) |
| 3 | `GOLD_LEVEL_ANALYSIS` | Per-level difficulty stats (completion rate, avg deaths, avg time) |
| 4 | `GOLD_LEVEL_FUNNEL` | Retention funnel — how many players reach each level |
| 5 | `GOLD_PLAYER_SEGMENTS` | Player segmentation (Hardcore / Regular / Casual) |
| 6 | `GOLD_DIFFICULTY_SENTIMENT_CORRELATION` | Sentiment score by level and death tier |
| 7 | `GOLD_CHECKPOINT_ANALYSIS` | How often each checkpoint is reached per level |

Since the frontend already talks to FastAPI (PostgreSQL), we'll replicate these analytics as **live API endpoints** rather than connecting to Snowflake.

